I enjoyed having the lamb kebab. The meat was a little dry and salty on it's own but eaten together with all the other parts of the meal tasted great. The pita bread is honestly the best part, they do it really well. Owner was really nice and accommodating to allergies.
Extremely nice owner, love the hummus, chicken shish kebab and chicken tutt

We placed an order via Grubhub from Tutt Cafe and picked up at assigned time. The order process was not smooth because it got canceled and duplicated when we were picking up our order.  The staff was friendly but not familiar with the issues caused by Grubhub which was frustrating. It was fixed in the end by Grubhub but was time-consuming.  We had their Green Pitza, Leg of Lamb Plate and Baklava. The food was decent especially the leg of lamb. The lamb was cooked properly with no gamey taste even my husband who hates lamb finished his plate.  We were disappointed with their baklava which was not the best in our experience and the filling was way too little.
Home made pitas and friendly service.   Standard middle eastern menu.   Outdoor dining with beer and wine also.
Great middle eastern food and service.  Friendly and courteous, definitely worth going to.
Delicious food for a very affordable price. We loved the lentil soup and the Mediterranean dishes. Great location and atmosphere. We will come back!

Everyone working in this restaurant was so kind and polite. The food was very good and I really enjoyed the atmosphere. When we went for lunch, it wasn't crowded at all, which was a nice change of pace. Highly recommend if you're looking for a nice Brooklyn restaurant away from all the noise.

I ordered a falafel-on-pita sandwich and lentil soup. The quality of the falafel was fine but the sandwich as a whole was not for a simple reason: few to no tomatoes.  It's the sweet/pungent tomato that makes fried falafel edible.  So I did not enjoy the sandwich, sorry to say. But the good news is that the lentil soup was excellent and I save some for today's lunch!  I will try them once again, and let them know about the tomato, and if they alter the sandwich, I will certainly change my review!
Great food and atmosphere

This place is great! I order pizza (and the occasional smoothie) from here all the time and it never disappoints. The staff are very friendly and attentive - definitely recommended.

The food here is delicious! I especially love the freshly baked pita! The chicken plate and mixed salads are two of my favorites. I never feel guilty after eating here. There are so many healthy options.

Tucked away on Hicks St on the north end of the Heights, this middle eastern joint screamed Egypt!   The usual middle eastern fare w many vegan options  The soups were good, especially Harir though the lentil soup seemed under-seasoned.  The beet salad was fine, the tabouli a bit dry and the falafel over-cooked.  Service was speedy and the place is kid-friendly.

The worst customer service experience . I'm very upset that as a customer who was ordering not for the first time was treated poorly and more than that. I made an order on Uber Eats for this restaurant and pre-paid everything at the time when order was placed , however when delivery boy arrived I opened my package and realize that all order was wrong and the food that was inside was probably belonging to somebody else . I was calling the restaurant and requested to talk with somebody and explained that was a wrong order or my order was replaced, gentleman didn't speak any English and arguing in different language  over the phone and past my phone to another gentlemen I explained that I paid for my food and wrong items was delivered he asked rudely "What is your location?" I said my location and my name he said " Aha NO we can not deliver your food you are far away for us !" I was in shock  what he just told me but it wasn't far away to charge my card and deliver wrong items.  I told him I 'm sorry you treating your customer this way but I paid for the food and never got my items he said : "Sorry I'm busy I have go, I have to go customer waiting for me" and hang up . I'm in shock, I wouldn't recommend . DO NOT GO TO THIS PLACE ! Awful service they will rob you in anything they can.

I now eat here regularly (or order in). I love the 5 salad salad and when I go with friends, we each have our go to combos. We reel them off high speed and yet we have NEVER been brought a wrong order and the food is always delicious. Everyone I have taken here has enjoyed it and asked to go back. It's delicious, good for any dietary requirement, and not at all expensive. The Harira soup is the best, in any season and in agreement with the other reviewers, Tutt's bread is out of this world amazing.

This Middle Eastern restaurant has been here for a while. The salads are very fresh. The platters are a nice size. I had the chicken kebob plater with bread and humus. It was delicious.  Starters are delicious. I had the spinach and cheese pie. And the lentil soup. Both were very good. Service is okay. The prices are very reasonable.

My favorite place tfor Falafels! Many other Egyptian dishes (and gyros!)  and the desserts are also real tasty. Freshness guaranteed and just a couple of block away, you can enjoy Statue of Liberty from distance and also Brooklyn Bridge! Owners are awesome, and hooked me up with free tea.
Amazing.

The seating area outside is covered by a loose carpet which hides the slope in the ground. One of the group I was with sat on a seat and it tipped backwards. He hit his head  and it caused a gash.
